Job Posting Title:   SE_Physical Build Project Manager_Professional
Description:

Physical Build Project Manager, supports the organization on planning, coordination and follow-up of build and test activities on projects at Volvo, securing a good status between systems and physical test objects according to project frame. Lead, plan, organize and control the Physical Build activities in close cooperation with the project team and PME within Product Development projects. This to meet the projects prototype need of Physical Builds and parts according to specified requirements.Physical Build  Project Manager on Professional level applies practical knowledge typically obtained through education and work experience. Manage smaller projects with low complexity or a part of a bigger project, with support from a senior projectmanager. May require the following proficiency:
- Works independently with general supervision.
- Problems faced are difficult but typically not complex.
- May influence others within the job area through explanation of facts, policies and practices.

Professional: position typically requires 2 to 5 years relevant experience

Volvo Group is an equal opportunity employer that values diversity in our workplace and we welcome all applicants regardless of age, ethnicity, gender or cultural background.

Job Posting Start Date:   2024-01-08
Job Posting End Date:   2024-07-12
Location:   Göteborg
Job Family:   Project Management  Support
Price: 653 sek/h

